				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">johnnie wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> What I am kinda uncertain about, is whether moving a 16 bit integer into a single byte yields a predictable result, even when the MSB of the 16-bit integer is zero (as is the case in my operations).</div>
<br />As long as the destination type is unsigned, it just truncates upper bits. If unsigned char is 8 bits on your machine (which it is on almost everything these days),
<br />
<br />(unsigned char) foo
<br />
<br />is equivalent to
<br />
<br />(unsigned char) (foo &amp; 0xFF)</div>

